# üêû bug report

### Description

When sharing a single module accross multiple lazy loaded modules, the constructor of the said shared module is called once by lazy module + root module.

This makes impractical to have a shared module having initialization steps, like dispatching an NgRx Action to check the user authentication, load server-side configuration, etc. Because the Action is dispatched multiple times.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-jwr53t

Open the console, "instanciate shared module" will be logged once at app startup and once more on each lazy module (Customers and Orders)


